    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I think it would be best to modify the design to accommodate the min 680px height scenario as opposed to scrolling the progress bars (sometimes the cutoff of content is in a place where there is no affordance for scrolling - i.e. no content is cut through - so the user might not see that some data has not been fetched if below the scroll point).\r\n\r\nWe have 2 options for accommodating the 680px size:\r\n1) We rejig the design so it is slightly more condensed - we use this more condensed design irrespective of app window height (it works for all window heights)\r\n2) We responsively scale the data fetch animation - as the user reduces the window height, we scale down the animation size.\r\n\r\nIt might come down to which is more straightforward from an implementation perspective?",
