    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@saledjenic that's a good point - reducing the number of categories will help with space for sure. The only thing we risk doing by grouping the data to more abstract categories is reducing the granularity of feedback to the user when types of data fail to fetch. The more detailed we can be on what couldn't be fetched, the more informed the user is on whether they wish to proceed without the missing data. \r\n\r\nFor the Wallet category for example, I'd be ok with losing my watch-only accounts but not my keypairs. So we would need some form of descriptive feedback anyway stipulating what has failed to be fetched within the broader category which in itself would take up room. ",
